title: Obama readies executive action on immigration
description: President Obama is preparing to announce new measures that would potentially allow millions of illegal immigrants to remain in the United States without fear of deportation, a politically explosive decision that could jolt Washington just weeks before the midterm elections, according to people who have been in touch with the White House. title: ‘Sick joke': UN Human Rights chief blasts US for helping Israel defend itself
description_full:
As Twitchy reported, Human Rights Watch head Kenneth Roth recently suggested that Hamas’ tunnels into Israel aren’t a “rights violation” as long as the terrorists’ aim is “to attack or capture soldiers.”

Today, the UN’s High Commissioner for Human Rights offered up a doozy of her own:

UN human rights chief Pillay condemns U.S. for supporting Israel's Iron Dome system: "No such protection has been provided to Gazans." (AP)—
Avi Mayer (@AviMayer) July 31, 2014

@Slublog @CuffyMeh The full statement is even worse. Makes it sound like US gifted these things to Israel and denied them from Palestinians.—
  (@neontaster) July 31, 2014

More from Haaretz:

[Navi] Pillay said that she was appalled at Washington consistently voting against resolutions on Israel in the Human Rights Council, General Assembly and Security Council.

“They have not only provided the heavy weaponry which is now being used by Israel in Gaza but they’ve also provided almost $1 billion in providing the ‘Iron Domes’ to protect the Israels from rocket attacks,” she said. “But no such protection has been provided to Gazans against the shelling.”

To clarify, the UN's human rights chief has condemned the U.S. for helping Israel protect its citizens against rockets meant to kill them.—
Avi Mayer (@AviMayer) July 31, 2014

What the hell.

I think it's important that we reflect on this tweet and consider the mystery of why Israel views the UN as hostile. twitter.com/AviMayer/statu…—
Avi Mayer (@AviMayer) July 31, 2014

And while we’re at it, remind us again why the United States still has anything to do with the UN? Because for the life of us, we can’t figure out why we’d want to be involved with such pieces of scum.

The United Nations is a sick joke: twitter.com/AviMayer/statu…—
  (@Slublog) July 31, 2014

@AviMayer @RobProvince Pillay is a raging anti-semite.—
Puim (@NotreDameFan27) July 31, 2014

@AviMayer seriously? Is she on drugs? How do morons achieve such high positions of authority?—
MAE (@impactinvest) July 31, 2014

@AviMayer i had to re read! All logic is gone.—
aline levi (@swiecamom) July 31, 2014

***

Related:

‘Sad sick man’! Human Rights Watch head: Not all Hamas tunnels are ‘rights violation’

title: GOP leaders revive Democrats' amnesty hopes
description: (DailyCaller) - Democratic leaders are welcoming efforts by the House GOP leadership to amend a minor 2008 immigration bill, because it could revive the now-dormant, business-backed comprehensive immigration reform push. The House's proposed change to the 2008 bill is "an opening for us to have a conference on our comprehensive immigration reform," said Senate Majority Leader Harry Reid...

title: GOP establishment on a roll over tea party
description: WASHINGTON (AP) — Add Kansas to the list of states where tea partyers tried and failed to knock out Republican Senate incumbents. Next up, Tennessee, and the odds are getting tougher for the upstarts.
